opic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   A relatively simple way to balance pets for good</span><hr size=1> It has been sad repeatedly that the primary reason for the balance inequity between casters and melee is due to casters not scaling properly with gear.<br>
<br>
Luclin with its focus items and FT have made some progress along these lines.   However these changes have for the most part only affected the rate at which casters gain mana.  Pet casters still do not scale properly because the power of their pets do not increase as they gain more powerful items.  <br>
<br>
One often proposed solution is to start putting the old style focus items into the game of various strengths. However that would require adding many items to the database, reitemzing mobs, etc.   <br>
<br>
The recent changes with resistance show a way whereby this inequity can be fixed:<br>
<br>
Allow a certain percentage of a casters Hit points, Attack bonuses, and AC to be added to a pet's values.<br>
<br>
This way although two pet casters using the same pet spell will not necessarily have equal strength pets.  Pets will scale with gear, and it will no longer be necessary to &quot;readjust&quot; them every few months to cope with mudflation. <br>
<br>
Respectfully,<br>
<br>
Traigos Ode<br>
